,Recommended,322920,13375475,"Posted: 15 December, 2014",all,Guru,"In laymans terms, this game mixes the Carnivores experience with a survival aspect. I found myself listening very closely for cues about nearby dinosaurs, as well as looking for dangerous foliage. The sound in this game is so excellent, it's hard to describe in words.This is one of the few dinosaur games in a long time that feels 'serious', in my opinion. There are a fair share of bugs (rubberbanding dinosaurs, some collision issues), but for 85% of the game, you more than likely wont notice an issue.This game fills a void that I have been longing to satiate for years. Highly recommended!Check out the video for a hands-on look (no terrible BG music or lame voiceovers, I promise!)http://www.twitch.tv/gamethesison/b/599497190EDIT: I'll leave this anecdotal part here5 minutes in, a Tyrannosaur charged me, drug me down a mountain, and feasted on my body. 10/10 would die again"
76561198154078334,Not Recommended,322920,15201473,"Posted: 4 April, 2015",all,jpaulsen10,"****** DO NOT BUY THIS GAME ****** ****** DO NOT BUY THIS GAME ****** ****** DO NOT BUY THIS GAME ******This game is absolutley terrible, it is underdeveloped, unplanned and was obviously just a quick scheme to get some funds for the company.The IDEA for the game was good, and I really tied to like it, but the application was horrific (I'm listing 10 reasons below)1. They simply took the engine of the previous theHunter game and added a few dinosaurs, no improvements on the engine or any attempt to make the game actually exciting (So yes I'm saying 99% of the time the game is Very BORING).2. Your character can't carry more than 20KG, which is not nearly enough in comparison to the amount of bullets it takes to kill a single dinosaur (once I shot a triceretops with 23 bullets before it dropped, and that is only ONE dinosaur, it took me about week in real life to gather all those bullets). I managed to kill 2 T-rex's due to the Clipping bug where they got stuck in the wall. They either have to make the dinosaurs weaker, add more bullets, or add more backpack space.3. Your character dies 90% of the time with a single attack, a T-rex (one blow and you're dead), the Quetzalcoatlus picks you up and throws you down and you're dead, the Utahraptor comes in packs of 5 or 6 so unless you're carrying a vast amount of bullets, surving them is rather slim (but carrying a lot of bullets is also extremely unlikley since you have a 20KG limit)4. You start off with a machete, which does practically no damage at all. They wan't to give you the ""feel"" of a survival game, but no options to build a shelter or a place to store bullets and guns you've picked up (since you're sitting with limited space on you as a person), also no place to purchase more bullets once you run out.5. The game has a purchasing system where you get money for every kill (upon spawing ONLY), but you have to be an incredibly high level to be able to unlock decent guns, which is very stupid since you start off most of the time getting killed in the first 10 minutes (because you have no way to defend yourself properly).6. Running is a severe problem since the character is so slow, he only sprints for 100mtrs and takes forever to regenerate his stamina. Your character weights 60KG in the game and normally people that weight can sprint a LOT further since they have no extra body weight to carry.7. There are practically only carnivores in the game, which makes no sense at all (Apart from the triceretops). If there are only carnivores, what exactly do THEY eat? The had to add a lot more herbivores as well example: Galimimus (for the herd effect), Brachiosaurus (big game hunting), stegosaures etc.8. If it is supposed to be a hunting game, then your character must be able to look at tree bark to check for trails, you must be able to climb trees to be able to shoot the dinosaurs from above, little shelters close to watering holes. I honestly think the developers themselves never even went hunting once.9. As mentioned in section 2, dinosaurs have the capabilities to fly and travel through solid objects like rocks, but of course YOU dont. Your character cant even jump over small objects (since there is no such option), making climbing the volcano mountain in the middle of the map extremely tedious and it takes MUCH longer than what it would in real life (Also I think the developers never climbed a mountain in their lives either).10. The game (if you still want to call it that) is REALLY EXPENSIVE $29.99, with the same amount of money you can purchase much better games than this on Steam, since the developers aren't sure if they wanted to release a HUNTING game or a Survival game. So they took the worse out of both genres, added an insane price tag to it and sold it to the community. They ripped people off with theHunter, and now they're ripping people off with theHunter:PrimalI normally don't complain about bad purchases, but seriously DO NOT BE FOOLED BY THEIR MARKETING (as I was), rather spend your money on something else.****** DO NOT BUY THIS GAME ************ DO NOT BUY THIS GAME ************ DO NOT BUY THIS GAME ******"
76561198069410693,Recommended,322920,17842717,"Posted: 1 September, 2015",all,Tintin,"The Hunter Primal. After reading dozens of reviews, and playing it for a few dozen hours myself I have come to some conclusions about the game. First off this is NOT a game for EVERYONE. Are you patient? This is arguably the most expensive tramping simulator out there... No kidding! There have been times when I've tramped for over an hour and not seen a Dino or anything of real interest except very beautiful scenery, but even that can get old. Or, you can load the game up and stumble across several T-Rex or half a dozen Raptors that tear you to shreds and cause you to lose all your gear that you've spent over ten hours collecting.A lot of people review the game negatively based upon the fact the game ""isn't finished"". The game is perfectly playable and enjoyable as it is, and is indeed ""finished"" it isn't however very ""polished"" and a few areas of the game could do with vast improvement, in fact a lot of areas could. If you need a slick, styled, polished game, this probably isn't for you. This game however is extremely immersive, and also very lonely.One of the great reasons for this game is the sense of abandonment, the aloneness, even with other players in the game. It's a harsh environment, there's big creatures out to kill and eat you, weapons are scarce and ammo is scarcer. It really does get the adrenaline going, which is a definite pro.Some say the game is easy, some say the game is hard. The game is both and neither. The difficulty is based on serveral variable factors, your skill at FPS, your gear (guns, ammo level, camo), your environment (jungle, plains, hills etc..), and the ammount and type of dinos around at the time. Sometimes it's near impossible to even stay alive, other times you're tramping around shooting things without a worry or care in the world. This is enjoyable as at times you can relax at times you need to focus more.All in all I enjoy this game very much, I wish there were more types of dinosaurs, and some parts were more polished but I very happily recommend it to people who fit the criteria above. Load up! Lets go hunting!"
,Recommended,322920,13379888,"Posted: 15 December, 2014",all,"Allen ""Captain"" Grant","I Alt-F4'd as a Tyrannosaur sprinted towards me.https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m5Gs15Y7UN8Full Review:Now that I have at least an hour under my belt, my initial impressions are as follows:Pros:1)Superb Sound design and stage. The forests and wildlife sound authentic, and the dinosaurs don't use recycled soundbytes from other games/movies.2)Graphical fidelity is great, but it's nothing to write home about.3)The difficulty is refreshing and adds a feeling of helplessness as you're pursued by otherworldy creatures.4)Based on the developer's track record, this game won't be abandonded. I'm looking at you, The Stomping Land.Cons:1)It's immediately clear that this isn't a finished product and requires more content. In most instances the game will spawn you next to one of the three available dinosaurs, which loses its charm after being mauled several times.2)I haven't been able to host or join multiplayer sessions. This will most likely be patched within the coming days before Christmas.3)Key-Binding seems to be a bit unorthodox. I found myself rebinding most of the default keys to more comfortable orientations to suit my casual play-style.4)Odd instances of AI-behavior and glitches. Despite being well-hidden, dinosaurs are inclined to walk directly towards you and into your line of sight; I also died in a pond reaching only my thighs.5)The Island is very large, but it still lacks a great deal of polish. More folliage and natural landscaping would do wonders for this game.Final thoughts:If you're thinking of picking up this game, wait until more content is introduced. Ultimately, I picked this up as a future investment, and because I just love me some dinah-saours. Consider this a future recommendation."
,Recommended,322920,13464072,"Posted: 19 December, 2014",all,MC_Strelok,"Me and this guy were walking around and saw a T-Rex, so we went prone. The giant god damn reptile walked right over us while we were laying there ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ our pants. When we thought we were safe, we slowly crawled away. After a few seconds passed, I heard a screen shaking, eardrum popping, massive sounding roar as I turned around to see my friend get devoured by a reptillian Satan. The beast then looked to me. We locked eyes for a moment, and a sense of understanding moved through me. It was then that the beast moved unto me, roared in my face, and ate me.10/10, would die again.But now for an actual review.After puting an extensive amount of time playing the game, I feel that I am ready to give a completely honest and full fledged review. This game, at its core, is very hit or miss. Some people will love it, while others will instantly denounce it for being too hard or a cash grab. While I believe the game is well worth the money, don't take my word for it. I will attempt to give the pros and cons of the game in a completely unbiased fashion, so that you may form your own opinion about the game before you buy it.PROS:1. World and Atmosphere. This game couples amazing sound design with stunning visuals creates an amazing immersive world. You can hear T-Rexes stomping around from miles away, and spot Quezalcoatluses flying in the sky before they have a chance to see you. While this does add to the immersion, it also rewards attentive players who can see a threat before it even knows they exist.2. Weapons and Damage Models. The weapons of Primal are very grounded in reality. All weapons match to their respective ammunition types and every weapon looks, sounds, and feels like an actual weapon. Firearms are loud, bows have believable ballistics, and everything feels very solid. Coming from someone who is very experienced with firearms, I can attest to the realism of this game's weapons. Also, being based on a realistic hunting game, Primal's damage models are very precise. Heart shots are king, while general body/gut shots will not instantly drop most of Primal's beasts. Overall, the guns are good.3. The Actual Gameplay. Primal's gameplay is very intense, You can go from walking through a peaceful field to being chased by Utahraptors in mere seconds. This isn't a casual game. Deaths are punishing while kills are immensly rewarding. Even with high level gear, carelessness is often punished with death.CONS:1. Bugs. While the games stability has been immensely improved, the game still has lots of bugs. It wil crash every so often, and movement is very finicky. Also, the only servers are hosted through other player's internet connections, resulting in high pings and short lived servers.2. Developement. Until recently, this game had been declared dead by most. The developers of this game are very invested in other projects and seem to view Primal of a sort of hobby on the side. On the up side, they have issued a survey for players to take and have also decided to try and tackle some of the bugs. Even though the game has officially released, they still intend on giving it regular updates.CONSENSUS: Primal is a great concept, but it is still in the making. While basic gameplay is good, there are still things that need to be ironed out and content that should be added in. While I understand some negative reviews, I believe that many of them portray this game in a bad light. Many people simply expect things from the game that it simply cannot offer. There isn't crafting or base building (as of yet) because the game is developed and marketed as a dinosaur hunting game. But, in the end, it is for you to decide. If you enjoy challenging or intense games, this is for you. If you're looking for another Primal Carnage of Orion: Prelude, then you will be dissapointed."
76561198008441499,Not Recommended,322920,16037871,"Posted: 28 May, 2015",all,kourcha,The game is not finished by any means
,Not Recommended,322920,15213926,"Posted: 4 April, 2015",all,CannibalNinja,"Sorry to say, I'm very dissapointed with this game. I went in with high expectations, i mean after all, a survival game with Dinos? that sounds amazing! sad to say it was not.Mainly, there isn't enough content. I can't believe they would call this finished. There are none of your typical survival game aspects in here at all. No base building, trap building, crafting, hunger, nothing.You spend the whole game wandering this GIANT map, (which wouldnt be such an issue if you didnt walk slower than a crippled grandmother), trying to find supply boxes (which mind you, are NO WHERE near eachother) in order to defend yourself against near impossible to kill dinosaurs. Then, hopefully, if you manage to stay alive long enough, you can freely track and hunt the dinosaurs. Thats it. seriously, thats all.Not to mention there are only a grand total of 5 dinosaurs in the game. all of which are carnivores. (minus the Triceratops) and if you get spoted by a Utahraptor, you are pretty much screwed. you have limited defense, and you can't run very far or fast. Its irritating.The enviroment could use some cleaning up aswell. As much as they are beautiful, and perfect for screenshots and such, they aren't very functional for gameplay. most of the map has very steep hills, making it seem like the player shouldn't be there. Its very rocky, making it difficult to manuver. Most of the terrain is uneven, water clips through the beaches at places it shouldnt, the water randomly gets deep in some spots and seeing as you can't swim, also makes it hard to move across some beaches, and rivers/streams. Not to mention you can't jump.You also cant carry very much, which becomes problematic, if you cant store your ammo anywhere. Especially when you usually spend mostof the game with far more ammo than weapons. (and more ammo for weapons you dont have)Honestly, I'm very dissapointed. The idea for this game was great, but it's far from finished and is lacking severly in content. ESPECIALLY when they want $30 for it.dont waste the money."
