76561198079889772,Not Recommended,322920,32448089,Posted: 15 June,all,Actium,"A unfinished game that is at this point just looking like a blatant cash-grab.The inventory system is archaic and not fit for a game with any sort of action involved.You need to go into your inventory to reload your weapon while a dinosaur is trying to bite your legs of.All you do in this game is run from loot-drop to loot-drop picking up random items.Congratulations you ran through a dinosaur infested jungle to get a T-shirt.The dinosaurs are bullet sponges and if you meet a T-Rex you are dead, unless of course you glitch the AI that has the intelligence of a brick against a larger than average rock or building.The dinosaur tracking system is ripped from their other game (thehunter classic) but unlike their old hunting game where you level up your tracking skill of each animal and it is made difficult on purpose for beginners to track animals with tracks leading nowhere, there is no leveling here and you basically have an un-usable method of tracking.All i can say is that -this is not the kind of game we were lead to believe they were selling."
76561198001558115,Not Recommended,322920,15163373,"Posted: 1 April, 2015",all,Dueoh Helsite,"Update 4/11/2015:They did a MAJOR overhaul on the Quetzalcoatlus and it made the game A LOT more bearable. Quetzalcoatlus aren't EVERYWHERE now (they only spawn near Volcano's and really high lands). This alone made the game so much better. Now you can actually EXPLORE the land without definite insta-death.However, every other issue I've stated is still a thing.1) You rarely see dinosaurs in a game about dinosaurs.2) You travel for LOOOOONG lengths of time (up to 50mins) with absolutely nothing happening.3) Killing dinosaurs is nigh impossible at the start of the game (i.e. Levels 1 through 5-ish)4) If you haven't racked up a few kills for exp and money then good luck killing anything after an hour.Once you get to higher levels (9+) the game becomes a lot more tolerable; but from a gamer point of view: Why would I want to keep playing a game if the start of it is dreadful, boring, and hard (in the sense that you can't really kill anything)? I mean, yes, the survival aspect becomes fun once you're higher level; but with that promise, why would a person new to the game stick around long enough to sift through the bane of this game?I know I called the game ""Garbage"" in my original review; but it's not. What it is, is unbearable (at first). And you'll have to put up with that unbearable irritation for a long time because levels aren't easy to gain (since dinos are rare to come across). Once you get past that, however, you could potentially start to enjoy yourself.- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -Original Review:This game is a COMPLETE waste of money! Hear me out, because I keep coming back to this game, TRYING to like it, but it's terrible. And here's why:-There's NOTHING to do:You spend, I kid you not, 90%+ of this game walking around with absolutely NOTHING eventful happening. NOTHING in this world can really be interacted with except for loot crates and dinos. Your objective for most of the game, survuve. How are you gonna survive? Find camp points that have survival equipment (weapons, camo-clothing, healing supplies, etc). But the map is HUGE and that becomes obvious when you're walking with your GPS for 20 minutes and you've literally only traveled a distance about the size of 1/3 your pinky finger. None of these camps are anywhere NEAR close to each other, either; so if you're at a camp and you try to travel to the next closest one, be prepared to walk in a straight line for about 50 minutes, with NOTHING happening.-It's nearly impossible to kill dinosaurs in a game about KILLING DINOSAURS:Game Story - ""You're a convict sent to a dino planet to kill as many dinos as possible to pave the future for potential civilizations."" Early game, you MAY get lucky enough to find small Raptors. You can kill those with the machete that you get for free when you spawn, and that's where you get experience and money to buy things when you die and have to respawn anew. However, the dinosaurs age within game, and after 30 minutes they're fully grown (your gps tells you the age). Cool mechanic, BUT YOU CAN'T KILL THEM BY THAT POINT! Fighting baby Raptors is likely to yield success, BUT your health is gonna be dried up by that point, so you're going to eventually die. HOWEVER, the timer for the dinos doesn't reset! So now you have ADULT raptors, which you can't kill because as soon as you get close to killing them, they run away; and there is NO catching up to them. You can run, but your stamia is a handicap BEYOND BELIEF! You can track them with your GPS (via blood trail, foot tracks, dung, etc) but you'll be tracking for at least 20 minutes before you catch up to it. The dinos can bleed out and eventually die once you hit them; cool mechanic, HOWEVER, the time for that varies and the odds are, you WONT find the dino that you wounded; but if you do it'll be like I said before, ""Tracking them for 20 minutes before you finally catch up"". Mind you, this is just the case for the raptors, THE EASIEST THING TO KILL IN THE GAME!-Quetzalcoatlus... Quetzalcoatlus...If you can tolerate walking around doing nothing for 90% of the game, and don't mind the fact that after 30 minutes, you wont be able to kill dinosaurs anymore, then I present to you, the one dinosaur, that ruins this entire game. Quetzalcoatlus. This flying dinosaur is the ONE major flaw that was put into this boring, uneventful, over priced, waste of time game! Quetzalcoatlus flys down, picks you up, and carries you around for 10 (Mississippi) seconds. Then he drops you and you die... No questions about it. You WILL die when it drops you. I've survived drops twice (I don't know how) but then it circles around to finish the job... Quetzalcoatlus is the primary reason this game is absolute garbage. You think walking for 50 minutes to reach a camp and get its spoils finally pays off. Nope. Quetzalcoatlus are ALWAYS around these camps. You can go in and get the stuff, yeah, but Quetzalcoatlus WILL catch you while you try to leave, and it WILL kill you. When you die your body becomes a pack of bones that you can come back and loot for your old equipment; but of course Quetzalcoatlus will STILL be in the area; in fact, MORE Quetzalcoatlus will be in the area! Because it seems like every time you die to one, another one spawns in the area! Quetzalcoatlus are only a threat in open areas? Oh ok, so my options in this game are 1) Be safe from them while I walk around the forest areas where's there are no camps to get equipment, little hope of actually seeing a dinosaur, and just endless walking around with absolutely nothing else to do. or 2) Walk out to a camp in hopes of finding things to survive and die to Quetzalcoatlus, walk out into the open in hopes of exploring this huge world and die to Quetzalcoatlus, or try to walk from this forest to another forest and die to Quetzalcoatlus.-There are very few dinosaur sightings in a game about DINOSAURS!It's so rare to actually see a dinosaur in this horrible game. You'll find tracks and other signs of them in your area, but they're constantly moving, and they're faster than you and don't have STAMINA ISSUES! You will NOT see dinosaurs often. So you will not kill dinosaurs often. So you will not gain money or experience to buy things that will help you kill dinosaurs... which are rare to find in a game ABOUT dinosaurs! There is one dinosaur that you can easily find though. Quetzalcoatlus! Just look up into the sky and there he is! Walk out of the boring tree's and die! Or stay in the boring uneventful tree's and NOT die! GREAT GAME!"
