 visuals, some of the scenery is quite beautiful.Good sound, the sound of a T-Rex stomping near me makes my whole house shake with the sound turned up!Great potentialCons-Incredibly high learning curve.Exceptionally difficult almost futile to play solo, turning some gamers away, and others to hacking/exploits.Obvious glitches and bugs that would cripple a live release (I expect they will fix this by release)No Dedicated Servers, and with the crappy hosting/client system this will keep many players from fully experiencing the game.Tiny pool of creatures to hunt (Obvious that more will be added)Small pool of weapons (also expect this to change soon; WTF no .50 BMG? SRS GIEZ)No combining stacks of ammo or healing sprays? (Fixed stacking now works!)Very low loot tables, crates need at least double the ammo/healing loot if not more.No jumping, climbing or swimming, cause these trained dinosaur hunters haven't learned that, and they can't even run very far.Any idiot can hack the game, at the very least, hosts need to be able to ban players from their servers, as one bad experience can ruin the game for people.Takeaway: Great fun with a few friends and easily worth 20 bucks."
