,Recommended,322920,13411765,"Posted: 16 December, 2014",all,go away to fear,"TL:DR > The game is great, if you liked The Hunter, this is an even better experience, and not haunted by monthly pay to plays subscription. If you're above the fence about buying it, just do it, you won't regret.Now to the review:First things first, i liked a lot The Hunter but i just could not stand the huge monthly pricing, it would probably be one of my favourite games if you could just pay it once and play forever. So, when i saw this game, i did not had much option other than to just buy, a game so similar to the hunter being pay it only once with no micro transations? I'm in!About the game> This is The Hunter on steroids, you are stranded on a wild planet, you've been sent as cannon fodder before the colonization, even though the lore is as basic as the Avatar movie, it is enough to get you going. You start off with just a bow and a few arrows, and you have to scavenge drop boxes left around the planet if you want to survive, and, while you do that, you get to hunt dinossaurs.Hunting dinossaurs is a bit different from hunting wild boars, the carnivores won't hesitate to have you as their next meal, and they don't lack the ability to track you down. Most of the times, it is best to just let your prey go than to engage in combat, if you lack the element of surprise, this is not The Hunter, this is Be Hunted. You will find yourself lots of times listening closely for clues about your foes as you crawl away through the dense foliage, not for the faint hearted.Exploring is just awesome as the world feals really life-like, with a awesome science-fiction touch as you see yourself orbiting another huge planet exploring a planet that highly resembles Earth. Bonus points for hunting with your friends, you won't forget the first triceratops you'll put down after a lot of teamwork, yes, the bow may not be the best weapon for hunting such beasts, but it surely can get the job done. Also, this comes to another point: can you play it offline? Yes, you can, but unlike The Hunter you WILL need some help taking down the larger animals and surviving the dinoes that hunt in pack, find some friends and do it together!Also, as this game is based off on The Hunter, a hunting simulator, you can expect long walks and some frustrating situations,, but that is part of the features, if you don't like it, this game might not be for you.Of course not everything is great, and, for now, probably we can blame early access for it, sometimes the interface gets clunky, or there might be some technical errors. I am not mentioning the lack of content, as there is way too few dinossaurs and guns to keep you interest for a long time, but it will probably get only better with time."
