,Recommended,322920,14333378,"Posted: 4 February, 2015",all,TrIcKsTeRR,"TheHunter: PRIMALOVERVIEWOK.... So theHunter: Primal is very very similar to theHunter (obviously) however the main difference are the fact that you cannot purchase anything and then equip them when you first start because it is not a hunting expedition, it's survival... However they have just added an in-game money system, where everytime you harvest a dino, you get money and when you level up, you unlock something in the shop, so when you die, you get taken to a shop where you can purchase weapons and whatnot before you spawn...But it's not like other survival games... you can't build stuff... you basically just gotta scavenge containers and bags and/or kill other players and take their stuff... if it's set to PVP of course...The graphics are a little better than the hunter in my opinion and who can ever forget the beautiful sunrise and sunset water colours... and choice scenery!As far as gameplay, the mechanics are buggy, but can only get better with time. The player movements are different from the Hunter the walking and running are faster, but they have introduced a sprint system which uses stamina and is extremely loud to attract dinosaurs. (Only use in emergency) The hunter mate (although called settler mate) works exactly the same way, spotting and tracking works the same but there isn’t tracking or spotting skill levels, and of course trophy shots and harvesting work the same way also. You don't get experience for weapon use in this game either...There is also a new tracking feature in which I really like... when you wound an animal and you track it's blood, it tells you in percentage how injured it is... for eg.... after shooting a T-Rex 6 times with a shotgun, after scanning it's blood it told me that it had 45-60% health left and the next time I shot it once... it said 30-48% (as well as body/intestine shot etc)THE GOOD- Great graphics- Excellent immersion (especially when the t-rex is nearby or when a raptor knows you're there and he/she calls out to the pack to help look for you)- Cool map with central volcano (no dinosaur game is complete without a volcano to set the mood)- Has major potential for many wonderful things- No pay to win, no money at all (except in-game currency from harvesting)- Injury percentage for prey- When you die, you can retrieve your goods from your old backpack... as long as no-one else has pillaged it!!- Thunderstorms :D- Mean looking dinosaursTHE BAD- Lots of gameplay bugs and a rushed full release from Early Access- Only five dinosaurs... T-Rex, Utahraptors, Triceratops, Velociraptors and Quetzalcoatlus (Dino-birds)- Scavenging gets boring and old really quickly - needs traditional ‘the Hunter’ mode- Controls are very stiff and sometimes sluggish- Bad framerates in high detailed areas such as swamps and dense jungle regions- Faulty hit register, (shoot the 6,000kg T-Rex in the heart with a .700 while it's standing still and it registers as only a body hit, where sometimes I can drop a 10,000kg Triceratops on the run with one .308 round to the heart, where the bullet hole is on the leg... Can be quite frustrating at times... as you die from not dropping them or you run out of ammo...- Quetzalcoatlus seem to be able to swoop through hilly terrain and through metal spikes and grab you, even though you shot them in the head...- Sound is a little buggy crossing from biome to biome- The Quetzalcoatlus, although remarkable are very annoying and frustrating to deal with at times...WHAT IT NEEDS- Need to be able to craft something, to build defences to stand a chance killing dinosaurs without dying- Needs more dinosaur species (especially herbivores) and less of the current ones for a nice balanced game- Need to see the Dinosaurs attacking each other... raptors attacking T-rex and Triceratops, Velociraptors getting taken by Quetzalcoatlus and the traditional T-Rex versus triceratops battle...- Maybe a 4 wheeler would be good as usually the game spawns you on the other side of the map as your friends- The T-rex needs to have a bigger roar like on Jurassic Park... to really make your hairs stand on end.- A traditional ‘the Hunter’ mode, to create expeditions instead of scrounging around...VERDICTOverall I give this game a 6.5/10, well worth $15 - $20 AUD MAX... but knowing the developers... they did such an awesome job with ‘the Hunter’... So I expect the same with this... So if you like the Hunter I recommend getting ‘the Hunter: Primal’, especially since Dinosaurs will soon be ruling Hollywood again, it's nice to finally see a switch from zombie survival for once.Also a funny thing... when you find some T-Rex poo, you'll notice it has human arms and some skulls in it... fkn hilarious!! Even funnier than that Jurassic Park satellite phone scene!!"
