76561197992636698,Not Recommended,322920,30341462,Posted: 5 March,all,Lt. Heinz Becker,"Honestly the game is extremely broken right now. I don't know why the devs thought it was a good idea to have a save file  that anybody could edit with notepad and give themselves unlimited XP and Tokens to buy weapons. Also the save file doesn't even work correctly because it will not save your level or inventory after you leave the game.The game has decent enough graphics and the gameplay is very similiar to the original theHunter, but the numerous bugs, problems, and game breaking issues ruin it right now. The only way to even get the save file to work is to edit it with notepad, but what is stopping people from giving themselves unlimited XP? You guessed it! Nothing.Another thing is that online multiplayer games lag so bad that a lot of the time players lose connection to the host. This issue seems to get even worse when more players join the server. I have noticed that when the server has 8 or more players, de-sync gets so severe with the animals that they will freeze for a few seconds and then reappear several meters away from their previous position. Imagine the difficulty of shooting at a moving target when this happens. Also, if the host leaves the game, you will lose any progress you made during that match because of the broken save file. If they would simply implement host migration when the host quits the game it would make the game at least half as frustrating as it is. Dedicated servers would be a better alternative, but at this point that is wishful thinking. There are guides on how to fix the save issue but honestly to me it is borderline hacking because you can be a new player and give yourself 1000000 tokens just by editing a save file.I can only recommend this game if you are a die hard theHunter fan and this game is on Steam sale. Casual players, it isn't worth the $10. If you really wanna try it out, be ready to deal with the numerous bugs, random level reseting crashes, and laggy online gameplay.I have also submitted a support request to theHunters support page on their website and one of the developers emailed me that they are aware of the issues and are looking into a fix. When that fix is and what they will do is beyond me. If you are interested in buying this game I would wait a month or two and see if they release any patches first. Fingers crossed."
