,Recommended,322920,20186494,"Posted: 1 January, 2016",all,[RX] Kersey,"This game I see has got alot of negativity, mostly from those who havent played the game more than a few hours and rage quit after getting killed a few times. There is no doubt that this game takes a while to get used to, even I used to get extremely frustrated at not being able to locate settlements with weapons. But once you start to learn thestructure of the map and the mechanics of the game, and you start to learn new skills and stratagies, this is an extremely fun and exiting game to play solo and with friends. The concept of theHunter: Primal is great, the graphics and enviroment is breathtaking and overall this game truly does deserve more attention. I highly reccomend this game to anyone who loves survival, dinosaurs, action and of course having a great time.For those who are just starting out, here are some useful tips:Survival:The Hunter Primal is all about killing dinosaurs, finding gear and most importantly, survival. You may find the best gear but if you don’t know how to survive and keep it, it’s pointless. If you come across a dinosaur that you are not equipped to fight, you must hide. The best way to stay undetected is by crouching instead of walking if you hear something, and lying in thick bushes if something gets too close… Around the map, you can find health canisters which you can use if you are struggling for health. So if you have one and you need it, don’t save it, use it! When you come across a cliff or steep drop, you should never take the chance of just walking off to get where you want to go, you will most likely just fall to your death…Killing Dinosaurs:Utahraptors:To kill these vicious beasts, it’s all about hitting them in the heart. You can hit them as many times as you like anywhere else and pretty much nothing will happen. To hit their heart, you must hit them directly in the front center of the body. Hits such as in the back of the spine or in the lungs (which are in the center of the side body) are effective too. It is recommended to use a weapon such as a pistol or shotgun against these.Velociraptors:These turkey sized predators can really mow you down if you are not careful, there is no set way to kill these, all you have to do it hit them and they will die… Using a machete or axe is by far the best option when fighting these things, although be prepared as they can come in packs of up to 12…Tyrannosaurus Rex:I reccomend NOT attacking this alone! You should always bring a friend along. (by playing online) If you choose to take on one, be sure to bring powerful guns and plenty of ammo. You need guns with at least the power of a 308 Rifle but a 700 Rifle or .50 Cal is recommended. When firing at this beast, you want to be hitting the heart which is located in-between its small arms.Triceratops:When taking on a Triceratops, you need to have a decent weapon with plenty of ammo, it is unlikely to attack you but you never know. When trying to hit it, go for the lungs, spine and heart. It is recommended to use a 700 Rifle or a 308 Rifle with plenty of ammo.Quetzalcoatlus:This flying dino can be annoying considering it can be hard to hit, the best way to take one down, is to shoot at its body as it attacks by swooping down on you. They are quite fragile creatures and can be taken down with as little as two hits from almost any gun.Settlements & Gear:Finding Settlements:It may seem hart at first, but finding settlements is very easy. When you start the game, you will get a “Map fragment” when you use that, you will be revealed a settlement on the map, all you have to fo is set a waypoint there by going on the map and clicking a point and go for it!Finding Weapons/Ammo:Weapons and ammo spawn at places called ""settlements"" these are marked by little symbols on your map. The best place to go is the settlement at the top of the volcano in the center of the map. This is the ony place you can find the .50 cal rifle, however it is still extremely rare. At this settlement you are likley to find shotguns and good camoflauge equipment."
76561198089186677,Recommended,322920,15240481,"Posted: 6 April, 2015",all,drw_online,"I haven't played it too much, but I can say that it is a very scary yet thrilling game, and I would probably recommend it to ages about 10+."
,Recommended,322920,24303996,"Posted: 13 July, 2016",all,Bifrost,"This is a good game.  It's not fantastically polished, it's not intuitive, it's certainly not much of a survival game in the traditional sense.  That said, the game is solid, it's fantastically atmospheric and there is a very definite survival component - don't get eaten!While I would not have asked anyone to make this game the way it is I would recommend this game, at this price, to anyone simply for the atmospheric value.  The feeling of being alone, barely armed, without explicit direction, in a tropical forest of towering, rain-lashed trees, desperately listening between the booming thunderclaps for the sound of a pernicious dromeosaurid, is masterfully implemented.  Genuinely, this feels like you're lost in Jurassic Park, except that the animals are realistic.  No six-foot, bald deinonychus masquerading as velocirapotors, but feathers a-plenty.It appears as though bets were thoroughly hedged during the making of this game, and the design choices seem to be split between a traditional hunting game, a survival game and, perhaps, some implicit marketing for the devs' other game TheHunter.  While I would have preferred a traditional hunting game with set hunts, bag limits, licenses and an out-of-game loadout menu, or a traditional survival game with crafting and hunger elements, this game manages to get all the core action elements of stealth, shot placement and an arsenal of weapons from a hunting game and combines it with truly phenomenal scenery and atmosphere, in a surprisingly streamlined package.I recommend playing multiplayer vs. alone - the community (who I have met ingame) are extremely nice, happy to help people out and lead the way.  The use of gear spawns around the map, as opposed to making money to buy gear which is bound to you, seems to be very successful in encouraging cooperation and sharing of toys.Don't listen to anyone saying that the game is abandoned - it still receives updates every now and then.  It's just not top of the list of priorities of the devs.  For this price, you shouldn't expect it to be."
