76561198020970761,Recommended,322920,17344469,"Posted: 1 August, 2015",all,tech-edit,"I bought theHunter:Primal during its' Early Access phase but it sat barely-played for several months. I just happened to try it again last week and wow what a difference! This is easily now one of my favorite games (and I've never bought a hunting game before except for Carnivores many years ago).The updates seem to have fixed the issues I had pre-launch. This game is immersive with the graphics cranked all the way, and there have been quite a few times when I've actually felt dread (like when I shot and killed a Utah Raptor with the .308 and a T-Rex comes over the ridge to investigate and comes within yards of me on my belly cowering behind a tree). You don't want to die and lose the items you've collected (like improved camo-clothing, Marksman .308 with scope, shotgun with slugs, etc.).The island it beautiful and pretty big, the dinosaur AI seems great, there are more types of insects now, there are birds and I'd swear I've even seen a rat scurring around on two seperate occasions.I saw someone mention there were no graphic options, and there is, you just have to go through Options on the startup screen rather than through the in-game Options available when you hit the Esc key while playing. Someone also said there is no guide but it's there too...I absolutely do recommend this game and I don't think we've seen the last from the developers.Brian"
