,Recommended,322920,14250675,"Posted: 30 January, 2015",all,FryingBullet,"I echo the sentiments of many of the reviews here - if you want a frag fest, go play Quake or something. This game involves stealth, environmental tactics and precision marksmanship. It's as much about when not to take the shot as when to take the shot. And in case you are wondering if the limited number of dinosaurs (currently) is a bit thin - check out the hours I have clocked up and I'm still figuring out how best to take down Tri's. Movement in this game is great - balancing the advantages of repositioning against the risk of discovery. And the scenery is breath taking - it's not the resolution of the textures that makes it, it's the sheer beauty of the way the island is laid out. Awesome work developer dudes."
