76561198050449449,Not Recommended,322920,14860866,"Posted: 12 March, 2015",all,McRibbed for her pleasure,"I honestly wanted to be able to recommend this game, but I just can't. Not as it is right now.The level system is an interesting concept, even though it's only a means of artificial prolongation, however... You need to be level 10 before you can even buy a pistol, which means you're stuck with a bow until then, and I had enough money to buy 15 pistols by the time I was ALLOWED to buy one (even though I also feel the pistol is over priced for what it offers). ""But you can find guns in crates and sparse ammo"" True, that is something you can do, but as it stands right now over almost 12 hours I've encountered more T-rex than ANY, OTHER, SPECIES, PERIOD. (And 90% of the time there's been one OR TWO T-rex in one of the limited areas where a gun is likely to spawn.) Currently, the rex tanks bullets from anything like a massive sponge. Shoot it in the brain, heart, lungs, intestines, doesn't matter; takes 30 or more shots to bring it down. Add with that the extremely clunky mechanics or firing and it does nothing but frustrate the hell out of you.They also camp on your body after killing you and if you're close enough to hear their footsteps then they're already walking towards you. They haven't noticed you, yet, but they will. Even walking they move faster than you, try to run and they'll see you, lay still and they'll walk up and stomp you to death; so you can forget about going back to your body to get your gear.- The level system needs to be rebalanced, badly.- T-rex are entirely too hard to kill, a dozen 12 gauge slugs to the chest, at least half to the lungs and heart, doesn't even phase it. Same with buck shot and .308, currently they just soak whatever you throw at them and refuse to die until you've emptied clip after clip into their organs. (Though I will admit I haven't tried the .700 or .50 cal yet, mainly because I'm not allowed to even buy one...)-There are only 4 species currently, and of those expect to see more T-rex than any other species hands down. In order of frequency, from most to least, I encountered: T-rex, Utah raptors, Triceratops, Velociraptors. They both need more variance and need to rebalance how many there are. I've run into 2 T-rex in one place at least 5 times; that's just silly.- You move so slow. SOOOOOOOOO slow. Stamina runs out very fast, regenerates rather slowly, takes you forever to get where you want to go only to run into a T-rex and die instantly. Well, not instantly, it SEES you instantly, then you empty every single round you have into it, face, chest, intestines, whatever tickles your fancy; then it eats you.- Audio, especially the rain, cuts in and out frequently. Textures also act very weird, mainly trees when they're on the edge of rendering distance. Trees looking like they're made out of netting is the best way I can describe it. Once you get close it fixes but during play it's no bueno.There are a lot of negatives about this game right now, it's glaringly obvious how unfinished it is, and that's fine. It's early access, that's what you should come to expect, but it is NOT worth buying in its current state unless you are an incredibly patient person. The game looks pretty good, it might give you some feelings of nostalgia if you played Carnivores when you were younger, but that's about it. (There's also no trophy room, like we had in Carnivores, and I feel like that would be a great addition.) I've tried really hard to like it, and been nothing but frustrated the entire time. Most of this stuff can be fixed, and hopefully it will, but like any early access game it's a gamble. It feels like a pre-alpha at the moment with the horrendous balancing and lack of content. If you like the game as it stands and think I'm being too harsh, I'm happy for you, you're a more patient person than I am, but I experienced 11 hours of frustration and maybe 30 minutes of enjoyment.TL;DR: As it is now, I strongly feel it's not worth buying. Wait until it's more polished, if it ever is, and since you don't know if it will be that's why it's not wise to buy into it now. It's extremely frustrating and there's a distinct lack of anything resembling entertaining content at the moment. Save your money for when it's more polished (again, if it ever is) or go spend it on a game which won't make you want to throw things out the window.UPDATE: Still poop. Only now it's ""officially released"" poop."
,Recommended,322920,15218743,"Posted: 5 April, 2015",all,Dumbfounded Polymath,"If you have an interest in dinosaurs and shooting games, this is a definate purchase for you. I have played since early access and the game has improved slowly and steadily, to the point where there is a decent amount of content.The learning curve is very steep for new players, even for a seasoned player losing all their gear and starting from scratch can be difficult. Don't let this put you off as the game offers many rewarding experiences once you get your bearings.You start off with a machete and must explore and loot settlements and chests to find gear. Once you have a few kills under your belt you may buy items from the store which strictly uses in-game money, there are no microtransactions.You will die often to begin with but with practice you can drop every dinosaur with a few arrows and then theres the other weaponry, which are all diverse and good for different purposes. Pistol, machete and .308 rifle are good for smaller dinosaurs, whilst Shotgun, .700 double rifle and .50 sniper rifle are good for big prey, like T-Rex.Killing every dinosaur is rewarding not only mentally but earning XP and money too to level up and buy items. When you kill your first T-Rex alone or with others, it's a very good feeling, and leaves you wanting more.Overall I recommend this game to those who are patient and can apperciate a good looking game, where stealth and aiming your shots plays a huge role. As I said before, if you are into dinosaurs in any way, shape or form then this is a must buy. Please don't let the bad reviews put you off, there has been significant patching of the issues mentioned in them. The game is very enjoyable as of writing this.9/10"
