76561198059779166,Recommended,322920,15159919,"Posted: 1 April, 2015",all,Eric,"Great game, with a few very hindering bits. Hunting is fun and suspenseful. There is nothing like trying to make your way through a forest while avoiding a t-rex, or finally finding the right hardware to become the hunter. The recently added Quetzacoatlus (pterodactly like creature) are grossly imbalanced and really hurt the fun significantly. Standing anywhere but in the middle of a forest means you are prone to being swooped off the ground and dropped to you death. The other dinos are fairly well balanced, with the exception of a few glitchy bits, like t-rex's biting through trees to get you. Another HUGE issue I have with the game is the stamina system. There is a traditional bar that deplets when you use it, however, it depletes extraordinarily fast, and refills quite slowly. you can barely make it 15 feet before your out of stamina, and likely being eaten by a dino. It is almost inexcusable to be chased by a raptor for 15 feet, be out of stamina, and then basically watch as it attacks you while you slowly try to WALK away from it. In a dinosaur hunting game, mobility is key, and it is really lacking here. If they took out the Q's, fixed a few minor bugs, and made stamina much more balanced, this would be a 10/10 game. As it stands, I give it a solid 7.5/10, and worth a purchase if you can catch it on sale."
