,Recommended,322920,13409776,"Posted: 16 December, 2014",all,ThisThing,"Has been playing this game most of the day now. If you like a realistic hunting game with dinosaurs, then you will like this. It looks good and has the right atmosphere, that make u feel that u are there. It also makes you sneak around a lot. The ""cons"" in this game, seems to be minor bugs that will be fixed anyway and the ""pros"" has already been mentioned. As soon (and they will) as more life is put into the game, I can't ask for more. Here is what I to see:1. That species roam specific areas, that are realistic to them. So you don't meet the same all over the map.2. I hope to see some function, that makes you feel you have an objective. Like to hunt a specific dino or with a certain weapon.3. Veteran or Alpha dinosaurs, with a nickname. Killing this is like killing a boss. It has to be rare. (1 per server).4. Hunger/Thirst/Temperature/Wounds <- Else it is not a survival.5. Dinosaurs has to be affected by other dinosaurs. A raptor has to flee from a T-rex. Triceratops from all carnivores and so on.6. Meaningless critters and insects. I know they're there, but we need more. The more life, the better the feeling.7. Herbivores that is just there for the viewing and gigantic size, like Diplodocus or such.8. The ability to make shelter, a fire and roast the meat, that u also has to be able to harvest. <- I know this one might sound a bit far fetched, but that would really upgrade everything and give u a purpose for the hunt.9. The simple ability to JUMP! Even if it has no purpose, but the psychological feeling of having that freedom really boosts the gaming experience. Imagine if you didn't have the ability to reload (like in old games), but by giving u the option to suddenly choose and reload at the right time, changes the game a lot. So a simple jump would do.I can't really say anything bad, as all my need has been fulfilled, even in alpha. The above is just hopes and wishes. The negative stuff I can say is just bugs that will be fixed anyway. I have waited since childhood for someone to make a god damn game like this, and now I have it!"
