76561198047310176,Recommended,322920,35257488,Posted: 28 September,all,Mr Ghid,"Recommended...BUT BUYER BEWARE!!!This game is kind of a hard one to review. Personally, I really enjoy it, faults and all. However, for many, those faults (understandably) would kill this game instantly. Do I recommend it? Yes, as long as the buyer knows a few things beforehand so that they can make an educated decision as to whether or not this game is worth their time and money.Just a disclaimer, I'm not going to talk about the game itself (other reviewers have done much better than I ever could), just let everyone know what issues they may have to face going into the game.I'm just going to get it out of the way from the start. The other reviewers speak the truth. The devs really have abandoned this game (they did post one or two patches a few months ago, but they did nothing for the game and the devs have been infuriatingly silent to customer complaints). In other words, the issues this game has seem to be here to stay. The biggest hang up for most people is the broken save system. The game is designed to save a player's equipment, health and general location between servers (which is nice because players can be in game for as long as they want, leave, and continue on when they feel like it with no loss). Sounds great right? The problem is that, since the last few updates, the save hasn't worked meaning that, no matter how many hours you spent in the game and progress you might have made, every time you come back you are reduced to the starter equipment and spawned at the same stupid beach. In other words, you would need to stay on for hours on end just to get to the point where you could kill some of hte larder dinosaurs only to lose it all as soon as you close the game. The fact that an issue like this is in a game that is on full release and that the devs know full well about it and are doing little/nothing to fix it is completely unacceptable.HOWEVER (and this is a big deal) players have found ways that this problem can be fixed. It's a bit of a pain but it does fix the problem (if you want to check it out, go to *** FIX FOR LEVEL 1 / NO ITEMS / NO MONEY *** in the discussions by Dumbfounded Polymath). It would be ideal that the devs do it themselves, but at least players who really enjoy the good aspects of the game can get it to work properly. And there is a lot to like here.In conclusion, this is a great game held back by a horrific flaw. The save system. Again, with a couple of minutes work on the part of the buyer, it is fixable (hence the only reason that I can recommend it) but the fact that it exists at all is unacceptable. Do I recommend it....yes...as long as the customer knows what they're getting themselves. My advice would be to watch some gameplay on youtube to get a feel for the game and its mechanics and decide if it looks like something you could really get into. If yes, the fix is pretty simple and you will be able to enjoy a truly fantastic and unique experience for reasonable price. If you're on the fence about it, though, odds are it isn't worth it."
