,Not Recommended,322920,14037813,"Posted: 17 January, 2015",all,Diet Sausage,"Until there's a means to play an offline, singleplayer game I really wouldn't recommend this.  Though access to the internet is not a problem for me, I am not a fan of purchasing a game and then being unable to play it because an update breaks the ability for the game to connect, or similar nonsense.The concept is awesome, and the gameplay itself, while it can be improved, would be good enough in my opinion to warrant the price, provided what I said above wasn't an issue.  Currently there is no true single player game here, as you are still required to connect to a server even when playing in a world confined to one participant.  Connection loss is a real pain because apparently, things like supplies and items' positions are dictated server-side, meaning while you may end up reconnecting to the game should the connection falter, whatever items were in your immediate vicinity (like, for instance, a crate of supplies I spent a good 30 minutes trying to get to) will disappear.Hopefully updates come along which enable more consistent play.  As it stands I am too frustrated with losing my sense of progression to keep playing."
