,Not Recommended,322920,14020782,"Posted: 16 January, 2015",all,Tuxedoorigin,"This game looks good, but as of now I would not really consider this much of a game nor is it worth $20. There are only three types of dinosaurs right now, raptors, t-rexs, and triceratops. You essentially get a bow to start and just walk until a dinosaur kills you. you can kill the dinos (difficult to do as the aiming is bad) and find other weapons in the game (far and few between), but there is no story and no progression. They say they went to beta to allow for users to decide which way to go, which likely means they have no idea why they made a dino hunting game in the first place other than that people will buy it. They have other theHunter games out there and my guess is the only way they are going to add more dinos is by making you pay for each new one. That is an assumption, but I have no reason to believe they will change their pricing model for this game.Like I said before this game is not even really a game. There is no story, there is no reward for hunting dinos, and you are not likely to win against one. Do I want a dino hunting game? absolutely, do I want to spend 20 minutes walking only to be somehow surprised by a trex comin out of no where and eating me, then starting a walk all over again? not really.edit:I wanted to explain this game more deeply. I still stand by my words, but that being said I think I was going at this game the wrong way. When looking at this game I was looking very much for a Turok style of go in and destroy a t-rex gun ablaze, run like hell so it doesn't eat you type survival game. That is not what this game is made for. This game is a trial in patience. You are hunting dinosaurs, but you are trying to hunt them like as if they were in the wild. You have to look for dino droppings, footsteps, and the like. It will take you a while to find one and when you do it will be tough to kill.Still this game does very much still feel like you were dropped in jarassic park 2 and expected to die. Not like you and the boys grabbed your favorite guns and beer and went out for a dino hunt. So now that that has been said would I recommend this game? No, not my cup of tea. If you enjoy hunting, but also enjoy the comfort of your living room, then you would probably enjoy this game."
