76561198061440097,Recommended,322920,15148606,"Posted: 31 March, 2015",all,RampagingMuffin,"This game is most certainly complete, unlike what other reviews are saying. The mecahnics all work, the dinosaur AI has been vastly improved from what it was, and the number of bugs have been greatly decreased. The Hunter: Primal is a game filled with content and the developers were (and still are) consistantly patching the game and it will continue to get better.The most important thing to say about this game is that it is NOT for everybody. This is a game that requires time and effort to excel at and most people will get angry or give up when they first play. It is a survival/hunting game where you kill dinosuars. why would it be easy?The thing I like most about this game is the suspense. You start out in an unfamiliar island, armed with only a bow (or now a machete) and you have to survive long enough to find better weapons and become the hunter, rather than the hunted. There are heart pounding moments when you are crawling through the jungle trying desperately not to be seen by a pack of raptors hunting you or when you first hear the stomping of a T.rex as it approaches you and subsequently eats you.The Hunter: Primal is best played with friends. Trekking across the jungle to team up with a buddy and hunting and killing a T.rex is a great feeling and it takes a lot of what can be stressful moments away if you have a friend to be with you.In review (get it) this game is fantastic and it only continues to get better as the developers update and improve it. It will take some getting used to and has a steep learning curve but if this game style interests you (and especially if you have buddies to play with) it can be played for hours on end.Plus who doesnt love dinosaurs"
