76561198043910686,Recommended,322920,13541894,"Posted: 23 December, 2014",all,|LaG| V!C!OUS,"OMG!!!! I hate and totally love this game. It is by far the most intense, at times, game I've played yet. It does have some drawbacks though which I will address in a minute. First, i'd like to congratulate the dev team that worked on the sound and graphics. Some of the settings are absolutely spectacular. My brother and I just bought it today and I found myself staring at a couple of sunsets and a triceratops roaming down by the ocean. They're so life-like.The utahraptors...don't get me started. They were so hard to deal with in the dense forest I finally quit trying to get my stuff back. I was almost there once. I was traveling a little gully and saw a pack of them ahead of me say 50 yards away. Too late, I've been spotted. I laid down and worked my way over against the side of a rock wall as they approached. I can hear them hissing and that weird growling. One just walked right by me.  My God, they're everywhere. I can see their tails. Okay, my screen is red and I'm am feeding them with my entrails. I love this game.The pros are the intensity is insane. There are long stretches when nothing happens, but the never knowing when something is going to happen, especially at night makes the intensity more enthralling. The sound and graphics are top-notch. The utahraptors actually herded us up a hill where we had no choice but to take a stand against them. Very real feeling of dread. Between my bow and my brother's .308 scoped hunting rifle we won. My brother ran out of bullets. I'm going to cut this short because he's back and we're going to play some more.The minuses are the stamina. It runs out wat too fast IMO. Should last a little longer, but not too much. There's not enough wildlife yet. There should be a crafting system to build a place to make a homebase. Or perhaps a structure that can be used as one. That's it for now.If you like survival games, some long stretches of just looting and exploring followed by stomach twisting moments of chaotic mayhem where hours of hard work can be extinguished by one bite...this game should not be missed. Twenty bucks and my brother and I are hooked. In the immortal words of Axl Rose, welcome to the jungle baby...you're gonna die!"
