,Recommended,322920,13465588,"Posted: 19 December, 2014",all,Shattered831,"This is a quick initial review after spending my first 1.6hrs in game, all opinions are subjective to change as the game updates as it is in Early Acess State.I had initially heard of this game from a youtuber by the name of DevilDogGamer, listening to him talk about it immediately peaked my interest. The thought of being dropped in a distant land full of dangerous prehistoric predators with the sole intention to turn the hunters into the hunted.  Dinosaurs have always been of interest, an while currently limited in the species type this game did not fall short of delivering an immersive experience.PC Specs - MSI 890FXA-GD70 mobo, AMD Phenom 2x6 1075T cpu, XFX 6870HD gpu, Gskill Ripjawz 8gb ram, WD caviar black 2TB HDD, Onboard Realtech HD audioRating - 8/10Pros:1) The game is beautiful minus a few graphical glitches I noticed here an there, nothing major however. Sometimes I would notice a few white slivers here an there as well from textures that haven't loaded. However with that said my GPU is dated an it still looked gourgous for the better part.2) Sounds/ambience - The audio for this game has so far been done in extremely good taste. The nature of this game forces you to constantly be vigilant and paying attention. You are being hunted after all, An with time the 3 different dinos become easily distinguishable between them. There is also the atmospheric background noise, as well as the terrain/movement sounds.  There was one sound I feel could use some improvement, which would be when the raptors are coming up on you. To me it sounds like a record player playing static and it keeps skipping, It's by no means a game killer but it does get kind of annoying after a bit.3) Each individual dino looks amazing and unique, I love that the devs took into account that many believe modern day birds evolved from dinos ( I agree with this but if you don't to each their own ). It's evident in the designs as portrayed by the feathers particularily on the raptor which raptor in itself means bird of prey.4) Tracking is easy for anyone, Your not going to walk up to a dino sign an sit an wonder for 10 min what it was. Each animal has its own individual sounds and tracks, it's very important to be able to decifer what exactly your chasing... or whats chasing you for that matter.5) Loot crates stand out, they show up nicely on the pda as well. With a bright orange color, an audio que and the pda dropping you rite on top of it they're hard to miss. I also found plenty of them, an while most had decent drops in it I'll get into my thoughts for improvements on them later.Areas of Improvement1) First an foremost to few weapons, I haven't found a single firearm as of this post within the amount of time I have played. I get the survival with limited resources aspect an that this game isn't supposed to be easy, But with the number of crates I opened something other then another bow would have been nice. I did however find enough arrows the T-rex probably would have chocked on them if it wasn't ultimately a pack of raptors that did me in.2) Non-stackable items - I ultimately died from running out of arrows with my bow, not because I didn't have any but because my stack of 8 had run out and in haste switched to my stack of 3 which is no bueno with 3 raptors chasin ya down.  Pick a number and allow us to stack it up to that, doesn't have to be big i'ld say 8-10 if you'ld like to keep it limited.3) some dino suggestions for the future - Stegosaurus, Ankylosaurus, Allosaurus, Pteranodon ( more so for ambience then to hunt ), Archeopteryx ( again for ambience ), Baryonyx.All in all it was an enjoyable experience and I look forward to playing it and progressing with it as it updates. This is the game many of us have been waiting for, and tho this is just the first lick of the spoon it's already hit my sweet tooth.  I would recommend playing with a friend, tho it could work against you as well depending on the type of experience your seeking.I will continue to update this as improvements and changes are made, this is just an initial review an thoughts of the game in its current state."
