76561198063814743,Recommended,322920,14064372,"Posted: 19 January, 2015",all,shanic77,"Open world, no hand holding dinosaur hunting game. Even though its still being created and updated, it has a nice level of polish. Animations look great, and the enviroment looks nice. Dinosaurs are scary, due to how easy they can kill you, but also scary in a  realistic sense because they dont always find you. Join a player vs. player server and basically play ""Hunger games: Dinosaurs are here too""Some of the most suspensful moments in this game are the moments when you dont even push a key or move the mouse, and  a T-Rex is walking 6 feet away from you. Do you move away, or hope it passes? You only have 6 arrows and 4 magnum rounds. Its choices like these that really are special with this game. Your not overpowered with machine guns, and you move like a human carrying gear.Throw some headphones on, and you can really sink many hours into this game looking for better gear, and hunting.However to call the game a hunter game at times can be tough, might as well call it ""TheSurvivor"" because you feel powerless at times. You usually start off with a bow and arrows but their is almost no way to tell were the arrow flys when you shoot it until you see the little ""smoke"" effect it makes hitting the ground. Making it a bit frustrating to use at times unless you like 10 feet away from a raptor. Obviously if your 10 feet from a ratpor with a bow, your a dead man if there are 2  or more raptors which is almost the case, so prepare to die a lot.Likes:-Dinosaurs! (Only 3 for now, but its the most requested 3 I would say)-Open world-Not an easy game-Multiplayer! Play with up to 16 people as teams! Or play against other players! (2 types of enemys!)-Player vs player mode really is scary with both threats everywhere, only using your ears and eyes-Your little screen device will give you subtle hints on dino locations, but not enough to feel overpoweredDislikes:-The Bow is not well designed. Aim and fire and you dont see the arrow in the air, only were it hits assuming you hit ground and can see the ""smoke"" effect. Makes you say ""Were did the arrow go?"" a lot. Especially since this is a starting weapon, it makes it frustrating when the game also spawns you near 4 raptors. Would be nice if it worked like a crossbow with some kind of indicator of distance and being able to see the arrow fly to adjust aim.-Sound design can be better. Its not sounds themselves, but were the sound is coming from. The Trex stomping is an awesome sound, but it seems like it just plays, with little sense of direction. A lot of sounds could use a better sense of direction. I can tell its coming from behind me, or in front of me but not to the left right or center.-There is too much walking with not enough reward. The best loot (Weapons) are only at specific camps marked on maps while there are random pick ups across the map but they always have decent stuff. Why cant the randoms have good pick ups? Makes me only want to check out camps.Overall if you like dinosaurs, and dont mind open world games, I would for sure reccomend this game! It will require patience as it is set as a hunting game. So dont come in expecting dino kill streaks, since every kill counts in this game.Grab your headphones and prepare for dino suspense that you cant buy anywhere else."
