76561197960887681,Recommended,322920,14041300,"Posted: 17 January, 2015",all,PSYCHOCAT,"Only 1.5 hours in but here's my impressions so far:PROS:Graphics, nice and moody with a great draw distance (think recent far cry games)Sound: AMAZING!!!  from the music to the ambient life so far it's very good.  *see below for my first dino encounter where sound played a big part*Controls:  So far it feels good to walk and look around.  weird not having a jump button though.Location:  Excellent so far.  Vast island with forsests, swamps, mountains, beaches, and I think a volcano (wasn't never able to climb up to the top to find out for sure but once again the excellent sound design tipped me off that something was going on up there).  Found a few locals so far.....an old beach log barracade fortress called ""Raptor Bay (I think) and an old concrete tower with some small 3 walled cells around it.BUGS SO FARFirst one was I was getting constant ""lost connection to server errors"".  I was playing in a solo world but I'm thinking that means you're connected to a single ""hive"" a-la DayZ.  I ALT-TAB out to find out windows was blocking some of the online features so I allowed it access.  and restarted steam but still constant disconnects continued.Got stuck in a hollow tree that was next to another tree.  With no jump button I couldn't get out.  Gave up after five mins....quit to menu and restarted and thankfully it started me back near spawn.FINAL THOUGHTS:I can't wait to see what this game turns into as it's development cycle goes on a bit further.  My first life ever led to one of my best gaming moments of the year.  I logged into the world and was awestruck and immediately pulled in by the excelent sound design and setting.  I myself love vast open world exploration games and the setting of the island had me hooked right away.  I wandered about with my GPS and found a loot container and arrows.  I followed the edge of a swamp set deep in a basin with mountains and forest all around.  I felt somewhat safe because I could see for a good distance in most directions.  Then I decided to climb up and out of the basin.  As I got further up the mountain I noticed some large trees with hollow trunks.  Thought to myself ""hhhhmmmm gotta remember where this is in case I need to hide"".  Hadn't gone much further when I heard.....something...... wasn't sure what it was.  Staring to get a little nervous I pressed on.  Then I heard something else......sounded menacing......sounded close...... ok now I'm scared.  Was this just an ambient sound I hadn't heard before?  I crept onward now looking over my shoulders in every direction.  Then I heard it........OK OK THAT HAS TO BE BAD....I then started backtracking to my hollow tree.....the only safe place I knew of.  As I headed toward it I heard the sound again.   I got to my tree and went prone in the ferns inside.  I then heard a loud pronounced dinosaur call on my left.  Then as immediately heard an answering call off in the distance.  My mind raced....ok this must be raptors.  Then I heard another call and multiple answers...... silently I began to pee my pants.  Each set of calls got closer and closer.  I crawled prone as far back as possible into my tree.  Then i began to hear footseps.  Then snorting and sniffing.  Now I'm in panic mode.  Peering through the dense ferns I was prone in I could barely see outside my tree truck.  I saw a shadowy figure flash by.  Then another.  Then a third.  The forth one was close enough to make out a distince outline.  That outline also was accompanied by a text box that said UTAH RAPTOR.  Ohhhhhhhh  Crap!!!  I figured that they were hunting me.  As I saw the figures moving by I thought I had given them the slip.  Nope.  One stopped right outside my tree.  Then a second.  Then a third.  After an eternity of about 15 seconds the 3rd one saw me and attacked.  Trapped inside the tree with nothing to defend myself and nowhere to go I didn't last long.I was that encounter that will go down in one of my all time gaming moments.  It was so perfectly set by the hostile undiscovered world I was exploring.  And made perfectly terrifying by the excellent sound design as I heard the dinos calling to each other.  I know that at this early point in the games development there's not a whole lot to see and do yet but if this is any indication of what's to come I'm all in for this adventure."
