,Recommended,322920,13982557,"Posted: 14 January, 2015",all,Charlock,"I've played about two hours of this game and, when I realized I had to be awake for work in 5 hours, managed to pull myself away for some pesky sleep. I am already thoroughly enjoying the game, despite the many frustrations of hunting massive, nearly unstoppable killing machines. I have yet to take down a Tyrannosaurus or a Triceratops, but can effectively defend myself against a Utahraptor or two.I'll say this, keep in the front of your thoughts that this game is in EARLY ACCESS, which translates to EARLY DEVELOPMENT and the people behind its creation are still hard at work on it. That said, I have faith that we'll continue to see updates as regularly as they can manage and anything they do, at this point, is going to improve the playability/enjoyment.There is a steep learning curve here. It really is a brutal, primal hunting game. You're not meant to walk into a world ruled by giant, flesh-hungry reptiles and come out an hour later not having been repeatedly mauled with a T. Rex head on your trophy wall. It's unrealistic to purchase this game and expect to kill everything you set your sights on.You start with a bow. Arrows do not penetrate dinosaur skulls.If you want a serious challenge, then opt in and support these folks and help make the game better. If you buy it, hop in and being killed often frustrates you too greatly, just come back in a month and see what's changed.Some notes on possible improvements (which I'll submit as Feedback in the game, as well):- For a dinosaur hunter, stamina is in short supply. I'm pretty sure if I was being chased by an eating machine, I could run  while longer than these poor saps.- Ammunition stacking is a MUST (Everyone has mentioned this, I know).- Swimming sure would improve my chances of not being dinochow.- Being able to jump would be an excellent benefit.- A starter knife would be excellent.- ""Harvesting"" would be much improved if we were harvesting useful materials from dinosaurs we've killed.- Retrieving arrows when ""harvesting"" would be great.- Traps would be really great to see.- Character customization.I'm sure there will be tons more suggestions, but you all keep up the great work. Thanks!"
