,Recommended,322920,13722628,"Posted: 30 December, 2014",all,A Fuzzy Object,"I would like to start by saying that I REALLY want this game to be good.  I know it is not exactly a triple A series, but some things just have to be added.To start with, there aren't enough guns and attachments for people who like to have multiple options to take down enemies.- The best example would be Payday 2.  It is also in the same category as this game in terms of subjective value.  The reason why I still play it with friends is because there are so many guns and attachments and every game is different based on the random actions of the AI.  You won't need to include as many guns as Payday 2, but 5 weapons is just not enough.  (I'd appreciate a 50 cal rifle like the M99 or M95 ;] )-The dino variety also hurts the immersion this game would ultimately have.  3 dinos is ridiculously pathetic (sorry for harsh words, but it significantly hurts the game in my opinion).  You could start with the famous dinos, like:+pachycephalosaurus+pteranodon+Parasaurolophus+Deinosuchus+And many others from the cretaceous period. Because there are so many to choose from, I'd add in more prey animals and I'd LOVE to see a Deinosuchus! The world needs life!-The dino AI is borderline non-existent.  I've found myself standing in front of many dinos as I put bullets into their faces and end up taking no damage because it did not notice me.  (Also a major immersion breaker).-The animations for turning is also a major breaker since they turn like I'm playing a Garry's Mod session.  You could look to some recent dino documenteries for examples.-As in games like Far Cry 4, there NEEDS to be interaction between animals.  I have not seen any interaction between animals ever!  It doesn't need to be extensive since it is a hunting game, but it completely destroys the immersion for me, in addition to everything else.-PLEASE reduce the zoom for iron sights! The use of scopes is almost useless because it has about the same zoom level as a scope, but with a better field of view.-Another major aspect that is missing is the nests.  I'd love to stumble upon a raptor nest or some other dino's nest and be ambushed by the parents!  I do not expect parental behavior, as in hatchlings and raising babies.  It doesn't need to be that accurate.-For the love of God please let us JUMP!  I've been stuck in weird gaps that I can't get out of because I can't jump!-The inventory system is an OCD nightmare.  The ammo needs to be able to stack.-The day/night cycle is choppyIt seems like i'm being harsh to the game, but as I first said: I want this game to be awesome! I had so much immersion during the first hour of playing, but seeing all of the immersion breaking things I've pointed out, I am almost unmotivated to continue to play.  I read that you guys are going to add in some structure building into the game and that would be awesome, but compared to the points I've listed, this is secondary.  What's the point of having structures if the dinos are so stupid, you could just go prone and wait for them to wander off again?  When it releases, you should do what Overkill does (the maker of Payday 2), release DLC for a reasonable price to add more content into the game.  New dinos, more weapons, more clothing, etc. Some of us are against DLC whoring, but in this case, there is so much that could be added, you'd need a triple A budget to make it a dream game.Before I finish, I'd like to point out some things you did well in:+The detail on the dinos are very well done.+The way noise works is simulated well+The way loot works is good for the environment you intended to make, though I'm not sure if the loot pertains to who ever takes it first.  PLEASE DO NOT MAKE US FIGHT FOR THE SCARCE SUPPLIES!!!+The guns feel good, could be better, but I do not expect perfection in this case.  (if it's a $60 triple A game, I expect near perfection)+The sounds of the dinos are also done well and made me shift into stealth mode many times!  I love it!+The animation for the T-rex is good, but I've never been lifted up as the animation suggests,+The bleed out is good, you've done this before anyway.+The hand signals or emojis are done well! I appreciate those things because it helps boost immersion.+For an alpha build, this runs very reliably, possibly due to the simplistic nature of the game in its current state.  it could use some refinement in terms of optimization, especially if you are to add all of the things I've listed.+The ambient sounds really helps with immersion!!I really hope you find this helpful and I hope you add at least some of the things I've listed.  If you do, I'm definitely going to convince my friends to pick up the game and purge the island of beasts!"
