76561198179380771,Not Recommended,322920,24168604,"Posted: 7 July, 2016",all,skarrmann60,"The setting of this game is simply stunning; the island and dinosaurs look amazing, and the day/night cycle plus the weather helps set the mood of being in uncharted and unfriendly land. Having the opportunity to simply walk around and appreciate the visuals and sound would be very enjoyable.Unfortunately, the positives end there. For ""the most realistic prehistoric survival game"", the gameplay is pretty garbage. Dinosaur AI is buggy (You can just stand next to a Tric and hit it with a stick until it dies, it can't turn sharp enough to get you), and there are needless delays in the combat system that create very frustrating gameplay, such as drawn-out reload times and a very slow turning rate while aiming.The biggest issue is the punishing nature of this game. You start with nothing but a machete, a very limited stamina bar, and a settlermate (a map/radar device), yet the first dinosaur that you could encounter could be a T-Rex or a pack of Utahraptors. After you die, you drop all of your gear and have to make your way past whatever killed you to get it back. That is assuming that you can make it before whomever is running the game shuts it down, at which point you will lose all of your gear and need to start over.It sucks that this game has been abandoned, as with some gameplay adjustments I think that I could really come to enjoy the challenge that the game presents, but as it stands, I say don't buy it.tl;dr: The graphics are great, the gameplay is buggy and punishing. Don't support developers unless you enjoy losing your gear time and again."
