,Recommended,322920,17149632,"Posted: 20 July, 2015",all,SampleMagpie,"Gonna try to make this review as short and informative as I can.theHunter: Primal is an amazing and fun prehistoric hunting game.The Lore:You are an intergalactic prisoner or something, who gets sent to an alien planet, inhabited by dinosaurs. Your goal is to kill everything you see, so that an intergalactic coorporation can settle and build cities and stuff on it or something.The GameplayThe gameplay is based around stealth and hunting teqnicues. Don't make sound, and don't be downwind for a creature etc. if you don't have powerful weapons or a shelter, you are gonna find yourself crawling amid the foliage from time to time. Sometimes you get eaten, sometimes you don't! There are a wide selection of weapons and camoflague clothing in this game. Each item being different and useful for certain situations. You will spend most of your time searching for lootcrates and settlements. The walk from each settlement/lootcrate can be long, so grab a snack while you're at it!Some people may find this aspect boring, but I quite enjoy it. It's peaceful and calming to take a stroll through the world of TheHunter: Primal. My main issue with the gameplay, however, is the low stamina. You run out of stamina pretty fast in TheHunter: primal.HuntingThe hunting is a bit... questionable to say the least. You would think that a Utahraptor would not withstand 5 shotgun shells to the head and neck would you? This is the case, however, it doesn't bother me at all really. In order to efficiently kill most creatures, you need to shoot them in the chest/heart area of their bodies. Most of the creatures are pretty tanky and can kill you whenever they like. So be careful I guess... The stealth mechanic is wonderful and adds more atmosphere and immersion to the game. There aren't many survival games out there that comes even remotely close to having as amazing of a stealth mechanic as TheHunter: Primal has. That doesn't mean it is flawless...Pros:Amazing map, arguably one of the best open world maps I have had the pleasure of playing on.Immersive atmosphere. It really feels like the world is dynamic and alive.Cool dinosaurs. I love the Utahraptor and T. rex models. The other ones are OK.(And they have feathers ;))))))) )Stealth mechanic.Has a decently sized multiplayer community.Cons:Sometimes very glitchy.Awkward dinosaur animations and AI.Lack of content.Feels like it has been abandoned by the devs. Updates once a year or so, and the only things they add are new languages.SummaryGreat game, very atmospheric and immersive. Lack of content, but it maked up for it by having amazing map and one of the coolest and funniest multiplayer experiences I have had. I reccomend playing this with a friend or two, really makes it more fun.I reccomend this game to anyone who likes dinosaurs and hunting."
