,Not Recommended,322920,14121116,"Posted: 22 January, 2015",all,Doc Corb [RCL],"You know what really makes me sad? having to edit a review. This game is effectively abandonware at this point. It's satisfying enough, but it's just at a standstill and assuming the devs will be forever.Summary: I really normally don't plug early access games because I've been irritated by them in the past, but as of this moment this game is a whole lot of fun. It's one of those 'survival sandbox' types, except.. streamlined? You have health, stamina, your only way of regaining health is rare-ish healing items and rare as crap mushrooms. You start with a bow and 10 arrows, bright friggin orange jumpsuit, and your trusty PDA map thingy. You pick your way through the landscape trying not to die and also find weapons/clothing/equipment at various ruined resource caches throughout the map. It's made with the engine of the prolific hunting game by the name of: TheHunter that i've played years off steam.TL:DRPros:Realistic AI: 'The hunter has become the hunted, hurrdurr'Satisfying gun/bowplay: Bloodsplats, you see your impacts and arrows sticking out of stuff.Varied-ish, huge map: You are on a giant subtropical island, swamps, beaches, mountains, and volcanic terrainPotential: TheHunter devs have been updating that game for years, and as satisfying as this is right now, wow!Cons:Servers: You basically have to make a solo multiplayer game to play, even if by yourself. As of this moment the only multiplayer games joinable are from folks who bothered to forward ports and all that. I hope that changes down the road as someone that enjoys multiplayer but also has a somewhat unstable connection.Steep difficulty curve: While by no means impossible, it so far has taken a long time to walk away from an encounter with raptors alive 50% of the time, not to mention with only a bow. I consider this game to be a DayZ lite, in that regard.Limited content: Despite my adoration of the game, as of this moment there isn't an awful lot in terms of weaponry/dinos to hunt/be hunted. 4 guns, I think 4 different outfits (counting hats and glasses and so on) 1 bow, 3 healing items, misc hunting gear, T-rex, Utahraptors, Triceratops.All in all I totally reccomend this game for folks looking for a realistic sort of shooter where you roam around and loot stuff to survive and prosper. It's a survival game without the eating/drinking, which IMO leaves you a lot more time to worry about the staring at the t-rex 10 meters away while shivering."
